translation: rTnalstahtsiestnneecrfmozCceotkUarniaioSruecStatement by representatives of the Czechoslovak Socialist Republic: The so-called "guarantees of citizens' rights" in agreement with the Soviet Union have no legal power or effect. They are no more than an instrument of aggression applied in accordance with the principles of the law of the jungle. The leaders of the USSR have seized the opportunity of a difficult situation and put forward this proposal as a method of ensuring their own interests. By agreeing to these guarantees, the Soviet Union has violated the Helsinki Final Act and its commitment to respect the borders and territorial integrity of other countries. Furthermore, it has undermined the principles of democracy and the rule of law by asserting its own sovereignty and interfering in the internal affairs of Czechoslovakia. We call on the international community to recognize the injustice of these guarantees and to stand in solidarity with Czechoslovakia in the face of this aggression.
